Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into
1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, sprinkle
over the @Black Sesame Seeds{5%grams}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a
single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

== Mushrooms ==

While the chips bake, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high
heat.

Once hot, add the @Sliced Mushrooms{180%grams} to the pan. Season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until
browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate
the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%grams}.

Once the mushrooms have browned, lower the heat to medium and stir in the
garlic. Fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Remove the garlicky mushrooms from the pan and set aside for later.

== Creamy Gochujang Sauce ==

Pop the (now empty) frying pan on medium heat (no need to clean).

Add the @Creme Fraiche{75%grams} and @Gochujang Paste{30%grams} and
@Honey{15%grams}. Stir until well combined, then remove from the heat.

== Naanizza Assembly ==

Pop the @Plain Naans{2} onto a baking tray.

Divide the creamy gochujang sauce between them and spread out with the back of
a #spoon{}, leaving a 1cm border.

Top with the garlicky mushrooms, then sprinkle over the Cheddar.

When the oven is hot, bake the naanizzas on the middle shelf until the cheese
is golden and bubbling and the base is crisp, ~{7-10%minutes}.

Share your naanizzas between your serving plates with the chips alongside.

Finish with a dollop of @Mayonnaise{1%tbsp} for dipping the chips in. Enjoy!